summary: I’m probably hoping for too much here, but what if Villanelle didn’t shot Eve out of anger or anything like that, but to protect...
body:
I’m probably hoping for too much here, but what if Villanelle didn’t shot Eve out of anger or anything like that, but to protect her. Y’know, in her own super messed up way.

I mean Eve was just a whole big mess for most of that episode, she was basically falling apart and I highly doubt she was thinking to clearly.

Except for being angry about Villanelle manipulating her into killing Raymond, after the earlier learned manipulation it’s understandable that she would be angry about that.

But otherwise. I mean she was talking about going home, she can’t go home anymore, and Villanelle knows that, Eve probably does to, but in the moment, well. So yeah, if Eve was just going to go wandering back there, trying to get home all she would accomplish in the end is getting herself killed.

And like Villanelle is an assassin, if she wanted to kill Eve she could have easily, but as others have pointed out to me, it looks like she shot Eve in the same place Eve stabbed her.

I mean I dunno, as I said, I’m probably hoping for to much, and I’m probably WAY wrong, but I just had this thought, that maybe Villanelle did it to protect Eve, and like next season will start with Eve in a hospital in Rome, and when she wakes up Villanelle’s there.

I mean I can just imagine Villanelle being like, “What? You were going to get yourself killed, I had to stop you.”

heheheh

summary: The fact that Villanelle insists while saying that she loves Eve makes me very emotional.
body:
The fact that Villanelle insists while saying that she loves Eve makes me very emotional.

“ - I love you.”

“ - No.”

“ - I do !”

I mean. She knows she loves her, and she is happy to. She also had the courage to say it, after Anna and everything that happened. She has the courage to trust herself and Eve to say this, to show a form of vulnerability. She is obviously hurt so bad because Eve denies it… Denies the fact that she is in love, denies the fact that she is capable of having feelings, romantic feelings towards her.

In Villanelle’s mind, we know that the all stabbing stuff was a proof of Eve love’s for her. I think this is why she shot her. She wanted to prove her feelings, she wanted to show Eve her love, to mark her like she did.

This is why I’m not disappointed at all in the finale. Kinda dead inside, because I didn’t expect this, but so not disappointed, I just can’t wait to see the new season, and what will happen…

summary: Villanelle and Eve are kinda the same, kinda different. I don't think Eve minds murder, she has seen and been present for...
body: Villanelle and Eve are kinda the same, kinda different. I don’t think Eve minds murder, she has seen and been present for Villanelle killing two people at this point and while it shocked her it didnt effect her. She was more upset that Villanelle ruined the operation than she was that Villanelle murdered Aaron. When it comes to committing murder herself though I think it’s something that she will only be able to do when needed. If Eve was completely against killing someone she wouldn’t have killed Raymond even when pushed to by Villanelle, no normal person is that easily pushed into hacking someone to death with an ax, but she was convinced Raymond was a threat who would come after them, and to play devil’s advocate to villanelle for a second he would’ve, so she did it. Eve accepts Villanelle for who she is, murderer and all, but when it comes to killing someone herself it is a last resort kinda thing and I hope that’s something that is explored between them in the next season.
